# UI/UX Design (Juli web)

Load via Focus for `web/` UI work. Companion skill: `.cursor/skills/standalone/ui-ux-design/SKILL.md`. Token reference: `web/src/app/globals.css`, `.cursor/skills/standalone/ui-ux-design/REFERENCE.md`.

**Ramp research baseline:** [ramp.com](https://ramp.com/) marketing + app patterns, [Ramp DS](https://ramp-ds.vercel.app/docs). Adopt Ramp's **product UX discipline**, not their visual identity (yellow `#ffe74c`, sand canvas, Lausanne). Juli stays pink + Inter.

**Token foundation ([ADR-015](../../docs/decisions/015-design-system-token-foundation.md), P1.8-8 target):**

- **Theme:** **Seller = light** (`#FEF5F6`/white, charcoal text); **Affiliate = dark**. (Inverts the prior mapping — pending P1.8-8 in `globals.css`.)
- **Type:** one typeface (Inter), single **≤6-size** scale; hierarchy from size + weight only — no serif/display or mono fonts.
- **Color (60/30/10):** neutral (60%) → Growth `#16A34A` / Loss `#E5484D` (30%) → pink `#F86BA5` (5–10%); Warning `#F59E0B`, New/Info `#2563EB`; each semantic has a background tint. Never color-only.
- **Elevation:** 3-step shadow scale — `sm` cards · `md` modals/popovers · `lg` toasts.
- **Motion (respect `prefers-reduced-motion`):** card entry (fade+scale, staggered), metric counter on change, approval→toast, loading shimmer, tab/route fade.

## Ramp principles → Juli application

| Ramp pattern | Juli translation |
|--------------|------------------|
| Restraint as authority — one primary affordance per band | One `.btn-primary` per card/section; secondary actions use `.btn-secondary` or text links |
| Role → Metric → Density → Action | Seller home leads with **workflow + GMV impact**, then ranked tasks with approve/dismiss |
| Savings-first dashboard | Lead with **estimated GMV impact** (`formatVND`) and severity, not generic summaries |
| Product-tile mosaic (bordered cards, 12px radius) | Use `.card` (`--radius: 16px`), consistent `p-4` padding, `space-y-4` rhythm |
| Typography hierarchy from size, not weight overload | Headings 700; body 400–500; labels `text-muted` / `text-xs uppercase tracking-wide` |
| Inline form validation below field | Mirror `LoginForm`: error text under input, `aria-describedby`, disable submit while loading |
| Card-wrapped forms; primary right, cancel left | `TaskDismissModal`, workflow modals: destructive/dismiss left, primary right |
| AI as agent panel, not gimmick | `AiChatPage`: sticky input, suggested prompts, conversational cards — no decorative gradients |
| Design-in-code with real tokens | Use `var(--*)` and `@layer components` utilities — never one-off hex for theme surfaces |

## Information hierarchy (seller copilot)

1. **Primary question** — What should I do now? (workflow breadcrumb + top task)
2. **Impact metric** — GMV 30d, `estimated_impact_vnd`, ad ROAS (tabular numbers, `font-semibold`)
3. **Action queue** — `TaskQueue` / `TaskCard` with severity badge + single primary CTA
4. **Evidence & detail** — `EvidenceDrawer`, overflow menu, secondary links de-emphasized (`text-muted`, smaller)

Do not bury the primary action below equal-weight secondary links. Ramp surfaces "review flagged" first; Juli surfaces "Phê duyệt" / workflow CTA first.

## Layout

```
Mobile (<768px):  max-w-lg mx-auto px-4, pb-24 for NavBar
Tablet (768px+):  two-column where useful (summary | tasks) — break out of mobile-only centering
Desktop (1024px+): sidebar or split pane for copilot + queue; do not only stretch max-w-lg
```

- Shell: `PageHeader` (sticky) → `main` → `NavBar` (fixed bottom, `safe-area-bottom`)
- Workflow content: one template (`SellerHomeShell`) with swappable panels (`NewSellerCopilotPanel`, `LeakageCopilotPanel`, `GrowthCopilotPanel`)
- Header chrome: mode switcher + alerts only in production; demo controls (`PersonaSwitcher`) belong in dev/settings, not crowded title row

## Component usage (prefer existing primitives)

| Need | Use |
|------|-----|
| Panel | `.card` |
| Sticky header | `.app-header` / `PageHeader` |
| Primary CTA | `.btn-primary` + `disabled:opacity-50` when loading |
| Secondary | `.btn-secondary` |
| Status | `.badge`, `.badge-success`, `.badge-live` + text label (never color-only) |
| Input | `.field-input` + `<label htmlFor>` |
| Empty | `CollectingDataEmpty` pattern: why empty + what to do |
| Modal workflow | `TaskDismissModal`, `LeakageWorkflowPanel` — focus trap, `aria-modal`, labelled title |
| Loading | `.spinner` or skeleton; avoid blank flash on home/chat bootstrap |

## Copy & locale

- Vietnamese with full diacritics; problem + recovery in errors
- Money: `formatVND`; dates: `formatDate` / `formatDateTime` (ICT)
- `data-testid` on primary actions, empty states, modals (kebab-case, role-oriented)

## Responsive & touch

- Minimum text: **12px** for chips/labels (not `text-[9px]` / `text-[10px]`)
- Touch targets: **44×44px** minimum (`AlertBell`, nav items, overflow menus)
- Workflow steppers: vertical or dot+tooltip on narrow widths — avoid 6-label horizontal rows that wrap

## Accessibility & motion

- WCAG AA: 4.5:1 text contrast on `var(--foreground)` / `var(--muted-foreground)`
- Visible `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-[var(--primary)]`; never remove focus outlines
- `prefers-reduced-motion`: disable non-essential animation (e.g. `.badge-live`)
- Semantic HTML: `header`, `nav`, `main`, `article`, `button` — not `div` click handlers for actions

## States (required)

Every interactive surface needs all of these (mirror `LoginForm` / `TaskCard` first):

| State | Treatment |
|-------|-----------|
| Default | Base color, full opacity, standard border |
| Hover | Subtle color shift **or** shadow lift (elevation) |
| Active / pressed | Darker fill + scale `0.98` |
| Focus-visible | 3px visible ring + offset (`focus-visible:ring-2`+ offset); never removed |
| Disabled | Muted fill, reduced contrast, `cursor-not-allowed` |
| Loading | Inline spinner + disabled (label stays, e.g. "Đang xử lý…") |
| Error / empty | Inline error under field (`aria-describedby`); empty = why + what to do |

## Anti-patterns

- Copying Ramp yellow/sand/Lausanne — conflicts with Juli pink brand
- Hardcoded `#FF1493`, `#fafafa`, `#111` instead of CSS variables (breaks affiliate/seller)
- Multiple competing primary buttons in one card
- English UI strings or hand-formatted ₫
- Desktop layouts that are only centered `max-w-lg` with empty margins
- Generic AI slop: purple/blue gradients, cookie-cutter three-column grids, lorem ipsum

